result.execSummary:
The defendant Bronson Harding Ubersox was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Bronson Harding Ubersox is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Bronson Harding Ubersox was found guilty of Manufacture/Deliver THC (>2500-10,000g) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(h)4.
  • Bronson Harding Ubersox was found guilty of Possess w/ Intent-THC (>2500-10,000 g) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(h)4.

miscConds.notes: Defendant shall pay costs in the amount of $268.00.

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcoholic beverages or nonprescription controlled substances, or any prescription medicine for which the defendant does not have a current prescription.
Defendant shall not enter into any establishment where the primary purpose is the sale of alcoholic beverages.

Defendant shall consent to a reasonable request of a law enforcement officer, based on probable cause, to submit to a breath, blood, saliva, or urine test for purposes of determining the quantity of alcohol or drugs in defendant's breath, blood, saliva, or urine.
Defendant shall abide by all other terms and conditions of probation deemed appropriate by the Division of Community Corrections.
Defendant shall obtain and maintain full time employment or attend school full time or a combination of both.
Defendant shall participate in any and all  counseling deemed appropriate by the DOC.
Defendant shall have not have any contact of any kind with Cody Bevins and Ashley Bevins.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA assessment and follow through with all recommendations thereof.

Resolution as in Plea Agreement.  Court finds adequate factual basis and accepts defendant's plea of "guilty" in count 1 & 2.  Pleas are entered freely, knowingly, and voluntarily. Sentence withheld and defendant
placed on probation for 3 1/2 years on each count to run concurrent.  In Count 1 court orders 3 months incarceration in the Lafayette County Jail with Huber privileges commencing 1/06/17 by 6:00 pm. .  Court orders an AODA assessment and follow through tith all recommendations of the assessment.  Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcoholic beverages or any nonprescription controlled substances or any prescription medication for which defendant does not have a current prescription.  Defendant shall not enter into any establishment where the primary purpose is the sale of alcoholic beverages.   Defendant shall consent to a reasonable request of a law enforcement officer, based on probable cause, to submit to a breath, blood, saliva, or urine test for purposes of determining the quantity of alcohol or drugs in defendant's breath, blood, saliva, or urine.    Defendant shall abide by all other terms and conditions of probation deemed appropriate by the Division of Community Corrections.  Defendant shall not have any contact of any kind with Cody Bevins and Ashley Bevins.
